5. TEMPORAL-WEATHER MECHANIC (the mountain + town distortion)  [core LOCKED; tables TODO]
=====================================================================
SYSTEM: FROGS is d20-ONLY. Speed = number of ACTIONS (not movement distance).
[LOCKED]
- PROXIMITY-BASED. Each ZONE owns its OWN SET of d20 weather tables. Zone sets get
  nastier the HIGHER UP the mountain (the gradient): town = faintest, the upper Steps /
  the undercroft = worst. NOTE (see §10): the distortion is a SIDE EFFECT — the Throat is a
  Tower being corrupted from its undercroft that HAPPENS to have a Time-Wound on it; the cult
  is NOT targeting the Time-Wound. The temporal chaos is the byproduct, not the cult's aim.
- The GM holds a REAL-WORLD TIMER/ALARM. It fires with NO warning to the players (GM holds
  the phone) — they learn to dread the sound. On the alarm, the GM rolls a d20 to pick which
  table within the CURRENT zone's set is now active ("the weather shifts").
- Players roll a d20 TEMPO at the START of their turn on the active table -> sets their
  action economy this turn. Example mid-tier table:
      1-2  Frozen   (0 actions, time skips you)
      3-6  Dragging (1 action)
      7-15 In step  (normal)
      16-19 Quickened (+1 action)
      20   Unmoored (double)
  Nastier tables widen toward the extremes (more 1-4 Frozen / more high Unmoored). Worst
  (the Wound) adds secondary horrors (spell resolves next round; damage before the attack;
  forced reposition).
- GRADIENT = TWO dials: nastier table-SETS higher up AND the alarm fires MORE OFTEN higher up.
- ENEMIES CHEAT the weather: Dagonites ignore Frozen/Dragging, or roll twice keep better, or
  simply choose — they SURF the Tide rather than suffer it. (This is the hook for §6.)
