=====================================================================
§20 — CONTEST ROLL LEVEL-GAP RULES [APPLIED — see GM Guide/Main Guide,
  "Contest Level-Gap Penalty," added after the Opposed Checks section]
=====================================================================
NOTE: while placing this, found the difficulty ladder itself is INCONSISTENT across
docs — Main Guide uses Hard -4/Very Hard -6/Nearly Impossible -8/Impossible -12;
Reference tables uses Hard -2/-4/-6; players guide archery table uses -4/-6/-8 with
different labels. Feeds directly into the planned codex audit (below, §23).
RULE: When a contested roll involves an opponent whose level exceeds yours, apply a
penalty equal to (gap − 5) rounded DOWN to the nearest 5. Minimum 0.

  Gap 1–4   → no penalty
  Gap 5–9   → −5
  Gap 10–14 → −10
  Gap 15–19 → −15
  Gap 20–24 → −20
  Gap 25+   → −25

APPLIES TO: contested will-vs-will checks — resisting compulsion, intimidation,
direct override of another's action/intent.
DOES NOT APPLY TO: environmental, stealth, lore, task-based, or any non-contested roll.
  (GM still sets those in the moment.)
STACKING: the gap penalty REPLACES the task difficulty — does NOT stack with it.
  Take whichever is larger (more punishing), not both.

EXAMPLE — Valerius (AP 30–35) vs. party (AP ~10):
  Gap 20 → −20. Alfonso (magic score +22): needs 9+ on the die. Hard but possible.
  Gap 25 → −25. Alfonso: needs 14+ on the die. Very unlikely without further boosts.
  This is INTENTIONAL: the numbers set up "find a way to close the gap" not "no roll."

