--- FINDING 4: "MYTHIC" HAS NEVER EXISTED AS A REAL TIER, ONLY AS FLAVOR TEXT ---
Both docs use "Mythic" as an adjective describing Master tier ("Master Tier (15+ AP):
Mythic, world-saving legends") — not a tier above it. Zero scaling differentiation between
AP 15 and AP 181 (see Finding 6). This session's Contest Level-Gap Penalty (§20, built
against a AP 30-35 Valerius) is what surfaced the need for a real Mythic tier + a -20
ceiling on the ORDINARY difficulty ladder — that's the origin of this whole audit.

--- FINDING 5: `legendary difficulty` IS ALREADY DECLARED CANON, JUST NOT WIRED IN ---
Its own last line: "Toryggs legacy uses this." Most of its content ISN'T actually special —
crit=x2 is word-for-word identical to the plain baseline rule in Reference tables AND
players guide (fully consistent everywhere it's stated — no fix needed, just say it once).
Villain Actions and Phase Bars are ALREADY present verbatim in Reference tables' own Boss
Mechanics section. The ONE genuinely new mechanical addition is the HP MULTIPLIER (Minions
x2, Lieutenants x2.5, Bosses x3; damage/DR untouched) — this needs to be baked directly
into the new consolidated monster table's numbers, not left as a manual step a GM has to
remember (which is exactly how "vibing the enemies" happened).

--- FINDING 6: THE TRUE "NOTHING LEFT TO BUY" AP CEILING = 181 AP (calculated, not guessed) ---
Skills (13 total, Novice-to-Master, 4 promotion steps each):
  Novice->Apprentice: 1 AP promotes TWO skills -> ~7 AP for all 13
  Apprentice->Adept:  1 AP each -> 13 AP
  Adept->Expert:      2 AP each -> 26 AP
  Expert->Master:     3 AP each -> 39 AP
  Subtotal: ~85 AP to master every skill.
Stats (Might/Agility/Magic/Guile): every build starts at a fixed 40-point total (confirmed
across every Standing Stone + point-buy); AP-method cap is 18/stat = 72 max; gap = 32
points x 3 AP = 96 AP, invariant regardless of build.
TOTAL: 85 + 96 = 181 AP to buy out literally everything obtainable via AP.
RESOURCE TRAINING (+2 HP or +2 FP per AP) has NO stated cap — GM RULING (confirmed): leave
it uncapped on purpose. It's a SOFT cap, not a hard one: by AP 181 the marginal value of
+1 HP/+1 FP is functionally nothing, so nothing stops a table from nominally "playing past"
181, but there's no real benefit to doing so. 181 is the meaningful ceiling.

